### Shipment Compliance Automation — API examples
### Use with the VS Code REST Client extension. Backend defaults to :3000.
@base = http://localhost:3000

### Create a shipment (only shipmentReference is required)
# @name create
POST {{base}}/shipments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "shipmentReference": "SAF-IMP-2026-0007",
  "exporter": "Shenzhen Widgets Co",
  "importer": "Acme Importers Ltd",
  "hsCode": "8471.30",
  "goodsDescription": "Laptop computers",
  "countryOfOrigin": "DE",
  "billOfLadingNumber": "BL-88231",
  "invoiceValue": 12500.50,
  "currency": "USD",
  "containerNumber": "CSQU3054383",
  "grossWeightKg": 1040,
  "netWeightKg": 1000,
  "packagingType": "Plastic"
}

### Capture the created id for the calls below
@id = {{create.response.body.data.id}}

### List shipments (each row includes openIssueCount)
GET {{base}}/shipments

### Get one shipment
GET {{base}}/shipments/{{id}}

### Ingest a document (envelope validated; payload is freeform)
POST {{base}}/shipments/{{id}}/documents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "documentType": "COMMERCIAL_INVOICE",
  "sourceType": "JSON",
  "payload": { "seller": "Shenzhen Widgets Co", "buyer": "Acme Importers Ltd", "total_value": 12500.50 }
}

### Run validation (x-actor optional; defaults to "system")
POST {{base}}/shipments/{{id}}/validate
x-actor: reviewer@safiri

### Read issues
GET {{base}}/shipments/{{id}}/issues

### Read latest readiness report
GET {{base}}/shipments/{{id}}/readiness-report

### Read audit log
GET {{base}}/shipments/{{id}}/audit-log

### Approve (rejected with 409 while BLOCKED)
POST {{base}}/shipments/{{id}}/approve
x-actor: reviewer@safiri

### Invalid ingestion envelope -> 400 { error }
POST {{base}}/shipments/{{id}}/documents
Content-Type: application/json

{ "documentType": "NOT_A_TYPE", "sourceType": "JSON", "payload": {} }
